    <title>ResNet</title>
    <url>/2020/03/13/ResNet/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>&emsp;最近抽空读了一直想读的ResNet的那两篇文章。</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Deep Residual Learning for Image Recognition</a></li>
<li><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1603.05027" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Identity Mappings in Deep Residual Networks</a></li>
</ul>
<p>两篇文章的感受：</p>
<p>&emsp;首先ResNet解决的并不是overfit的问题。overfit是在训练集上有很好的效果，但是在测试集上很弱。然而，很深的CNN网络在训练时收敛时的性能在训练集上都达不到浅网络的效果。</p>
<a id="more"></a>
<p>​    其次，引入shortcut实际上没有完全进行identity map的工作，因为如果shortcut只能完成identity map的工作的话，深网络的性能的上限就是浅网络的性能（一个浅网络加上若干层shortcut构建一个深网络），但是引入shortcut后深网络的性能其实是超过浅网络的，换句话说，学习到的残差$F(x)=H(x)-x$不可能完全为0，并未完全实现identity map。</p>
<p>​    个人认为，直观上，ResNet较为优异的性能来源于网络最后既可以学习到高层语义特征，也可以较好的学习到底层特征，而且反向传播时梯度信息可以方便的反馈到前边任何一层。但是，这还只能粗略的解释其较优异性能，就其数学本质而言，有的人认为ResNet相较于普通的CNN具有一定的差分方程自适应性，几何上相当于构造了更平滑的流形解空间，从而具有更好的收敛性。</p>
<p>​     其实在ReLU之前，在HighwayNet文章中已经有类似的结构，甚至ResNet就是HighwayNet的一种特例，也即，ResNet的解空间的只是HighwayNet解空间的子集。那么为什么HighwayNet的性能反而不如ResNet呢？作者在第二篇文章中给出的答案是，HighwayNet的类似于LSTM的gate机制过于复杂，更难优化，换句说，”keeping a “clean” information path”更重要。</p>
<p>细节：</p>
<p>Q:shortcut connection时feature map的size和channel不同怎么处理？</p>
<p>A:处理方法有两种</p>
<ul>
<li>直接补上全是0的feature map</li>
<li>进行线性变换对size进行调整（文中并未直接使用线性变换矩阵，而是使用了1*1 conv同时处理size和channel的不匹配）</li>
</ul>
<p>Q:shortcut connection的类型？</p>
<p>A:文中探讨了三种shortcut connection的类型</p>
<ul>
<li>在dimension相同的shortcut直接相加，dimension不同的shortcut补0</li>
<li>在dimension相同的shortcut直接相加，dimension不同的用1*1 conv</li>
<li>对所有的shortcut都用1*1 conv</li>
</ul>
<p>其他：</p>
<ul>
<li><p>并未使用MaxPool来压缩feature map，而是直接使用stride=2的3*3 conv来压缩</p>
</li>
<li><p>关于BN层、ReLU层、conv层，作者在第二篇文章中有详尽的讨论，这里采用(e) full pre-activationh</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>结果：</p>
<p>因为我按照文中0.1的初始learning_rate后训练初期loss剧烈振荡，最后收敛也卡在0.2，测试效果也不好（可能是我选用的optimizer和其他细节跟文中的也不太一样？）。最后初始learning_rate设在了0.01，然后每次乘0.1下降3次，最后loss收敛在0.05附近。但是测试的性能跟文中的还是差了一点。</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Accuracy of the network on the 10000 test images: 90 %<br>Accuracy of plane : 91 %<br>Accuracy of   car : 95 %<br>Accuracy of  bird : 86 %<br>Accuracy of   cat : 78 %<br>Accuracy of  deer : 90 %<br>Accuracy of   dog : 84 %<br>Accuracy of  frog : 93 %<br>Accuracy of horse : 91 %<br>Accuracy of  ship : 95 %<br>Accuracy of truck : 93 %</p>
</blockquote>
<figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torch</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torch.nn <span class="keyword">as</span> nn</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torch.nn.functional <span class="keyword">as</span> F</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torch.nn.init <span class="keyword">as</span> init</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torch.optim <span class="keyword">as</span> optim</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torchvision.transforms <span class="keyword">as</span> transforms</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> torchvision</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> torch.autograd <span class="keyword">import</span> Variable</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> numpy <span class="keyword">as</span> np</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">from</span> tqdm <span class="keyword">import</span> tqdm</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">'''</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">ResNet32V2 with full pre-activation on CIFAR10</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="string">'''</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">LR = <span class="number">0.01</span></span><br><span class="line">BATCH_SIZE = <span class="number">100</span></span><br><span class="line">EPOCHS = <span class="number">160</span></span><br><span class="line">MODEL_PATH = <span class="string">'ResNet32_cifar10.pkl'</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">transform = transforms.Compose(</span><br><span class="line">    [transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(),</span><br><span class="line">     transforms.RandomCrop(<span class="number">32</span>, <span class="number">4</span>),</span><br><span class="line">        transforms.ToTensor(),</span><br><span class="line">     transforms.Normalize((<span class="number">0.5</span>, <span class="number">0.5</span>, <span class="number">0.5</span>), (<span class="number">0.5</span>, <span class="number">0.5</span>, <span class="number">0.5</span>))</span><br><span class="line">     ])</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">trainset = torchvision.datasets.CIFAR10(root=<span class="string">'./'</span>, train=<span class="literal">True</span>,</span><br><span class="line">                                        download=<span class="literal">False</span>, transform=transform)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">testset = torchvision.datasets.CIFAR10(root=<span class="string">'./'</span>, train=<span class="literal">False</span>,</span><br><span class="line">                                       download=<span class="literal">False</span>, transform=transform)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">trainloader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(trainset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,</span><br><span class="line">                                          shuffle=<span class="literal">True</span>, num_workers=<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">testloader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(testset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE,</span><br><span class="line">                                         shuffle=<span class="literal">False</span>, num_workers=<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">classes = (<span class="string">'plane'</span>, <span class="string">'car'</span>, <span class="string">'bird'</span>, <span class="string">'cat'</span>,</span><br><span class="line">           <span class="string">'deer'</span>, <span class="string">'dog'</span>, <span class="string">'frog'</span>, <span class="string">'horse'</span>, <span class="string">'ship'</span>, <span class="string">'truck'</span>)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title">BuildingBlock</span><span class="params">(nn.Module)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__init__</span><span class="params">(self, in_chs, out_chs, shortcut_type=<span class="number">0</span>, k_size=<span class="number">3</span>, pd_size=<span class="number">1</span>, stride=<span class="number">1</span>)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">        super(BuildingBlock, self).__init__()</span><br><span class="line">        self.plain = nn.Sequential(</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="comment"># full pre-activation</span></span><br><span class="line">            nn.BatchNorm2d(in_chs),</span><br><span class="line">            nn.ReLU(<span class="literal">True</span>),</span><br><span class="line">            nn.Conv2d(in_chs, out_chs, kernel_size=k_size,</span><br><span class="line">                      padding=pd_size, stride=stride),</span><br><span class="line">            nn.BatchNorm2d(out_chs),</span><br><span class="line">            nn.ReLU(<span class="literal">True</span>),</span><br><span class="line">            nn.Conv2d(out_chs, out_chs, kernel_size=k_size, padding=pd_size),</span><br><span class="line">        )</span><br><span class="line">        self.shortcut = nn.Conv2d(in_chs, out_chs, <span class="number">1</span>, stride=<span class="number">2</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        self.shortcut_type = shortcut_type</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">forward</span><span class="params">(self, x)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">        out = self.plain(x)</span><br><span class="line">        out += self.shortcut(x) <span class="keyword">if</span> self.shortcut_type == <span class="number">1</span> <span class="keyword">else</span> x</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> out</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="class"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title">ResNet32</span><span class="params">(nn.Module)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">__init__</span><span class="params">(self)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">        super(ResNet32, self).__init__()</span><br><span class="line">        self.convLayers = [nn.Conv2d(<span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">16</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, stride=<span class="number">1</span>, padding=<span class="number">1</span>)]</span><br><span class="line">        temChs = <span class="number">16</span></span><br><span class="line">        nxtChs = <span class="number">16</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">for</span> i <span class="keyword">in</span> range(<span class="number">3</span>):</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">for</span> j <span class="keyword">in</span> range(<span class="number">5</span>):</span><br><span class="line">                self.convLayers.append(BuildingBlock(</span><br><span class="line">                    temChs, nxtChs, j == <span class="number">0</span> <span class="keyword">and</span> i &gt; <span class="number">0</span>, stride=(<span class="number">2</span> <span class="keyword">if</span> (j == <span class="number">0</span> <span class="keyword">and</span> i &gt; <span class="number">0</span>) <span class="keyword">else</span> <span class="number">1</span>)))</span><br><span class="line">                temChs = nxtChs</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="comment"># 16-&gt;32-&gt;64</span></span><br><span class="line">            nxtChs *= <span class="number">2</span></span><br><span class="line">        self.convLayers = nn.Sequential(*self.convLayers)</span><br><span class="line">        self.avgPool = nn.AvgPool2d(<span class="number">8</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        self.fcLayer = nn.Sequential(</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="comment"># nn.BatchNorm1d(10, affine=True),</span></span><br><span class="line">            nn.Linear(<span class="number">64</span>, <span class="number">10</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        )</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="function"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title">forward</span><span class="params">(self, x)</span>:</span></span><br><span class="line">        out = self.convLayers(x)</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># print('xxxx', out.size())</span></span><br><span class="line">        out = self.avgPool(out)</span><br><span class="line">        out = out.view(out.size(<span class="number">0</span>), <span class="number">-1</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        out = self.fcLayer(out)</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> out</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">if</span> __name__ == <span class="string">"__main__"</span>:</span><br><span class="line">    net = ResNet32()</span><br><span class="line">    </span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()</span><br><span class="line">    optimizer = optim.Adam(net.parameters(), lr=LR)</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment"># scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau(optimizer, patience=2, verbose=True,threshold=0.1)</span></span><br><span class="line">    lr_scheduler = torch.optim.lr_scheduler.MultiStepLR(optimizer,milestones=[<span class="number">60</span>,<span class="number">100</span>,<span class="number">135</span>])</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    device = torch.device(<span class="string">"cuda:0"</span> <span class="keyword">if</span> torch.cuda.is_available() <span class="keyword">else</span> <span class="string">"cpu"</span>)</span><br><span class="line">    print(device)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    pretrained = <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">if</span> pretrained:</span><br><span class="line">        net.load_state_dict(torch.load(MODEL_PATH))</span><br><span class="line">        print(<span class="string">'load pretrained model'</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        net.to(device)</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">else</span>:</span><br><span class="line">        net.train()</span><br><span class="line">        net.to(device)</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">for</span> epc <span class="keyword">in</span> range(EPOCHS):</span><br><span class="line">            running_loss = <span class="number">0.</span></span><br><span class="line">            cnt = <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">for</span> data <span class="keyword">in</span> tqdm(torch.utils.data.DataLoader(</span><br><span class="line">                trainset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=<span class="literal">True</span>, num_workers=<span class="number">2</span>), <span class="number">0</span>):</span><br><span class="line">                inputs, labels = data</span><br><span class="line">                inputs, labels = inputs.to(device), labels.to(device)</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">                optimizer.zero_grad()</span><br><span class="line">                outputs = net(inputs)</span><br><span class="line">                loss = criterion(outputs, labels)</span><br><span class="line">                loss.backward()</span><br><span class="line">                optimizer.step()</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">                cnt += <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">                running_loss += loss.item()</span><br><span class="line">                <span class="comment"># print('[%d, %5d] loss: %.4f' %</span></span><br><span class="line">                <span class="comment">#       (epc + 1, (i+1)*BATCH_SIZE, running_loss/cnt))</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">            print(<span class="string">'[%d] loss: %.4f'</span> %</span><br><span class="line">                      (epc + <span class="number">1</span>, running_loss/cnt))</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">            <span class="comment"># scheduler.step(running_loss)</span></span><br><span class="line">            lr_scheduler.step()</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">            print(<span class="string">'using LR'</span>,lr_scheduler.get_lr())</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="comment"># print('using LR',scheduler._last_lr)</span></span><br><span class="line">        print(<span class="string">'Finished Training'</span>)</span><br><span class="line">        torch.save(net.state_dict(), MODEL_PATH)</span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="comment"># print(net)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    net.eval()</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    correct, total = <span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">with</span> torch.no_grad():</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">for</span> data <span class="keyword">in</span> testloader:</span><br><span class="line">            images, labels = data</span><br><span class="line">            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)</span><br><span class="line">            outputs = net(images)</span><br><span class="line">            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs, dim=<span class="number">1</span>)</span><br><span class="line">            total += labels.size(<span class="number">0</span>)</span><br><span class="line">            correct += (predicted == labels).sum().item()</span><br><span class="line">    print(<span class="string">'Accuracy of the network on the 10000 test images: %d %%'</span> % (</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="number">100</span> * correct / total))</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    class_correct = list(<span class="number">0.</span> <span class="keyword">for</span> i <span class="keyword">in</span> range(<span class="number">10</span>))</span><br><span class="line">    class_total = list(<span class="number">0.</span> <span class="keyword">for</span> i <span class="keyword">in</span> range(<span class="number">10</span>))</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">with</span> torch.no_grad():</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">for</span> data <span class="keyword">in</span> testloader:</span><br><span class="line">            images, labels = data</span><br><span class="line">            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)</span><br><span class="line">            outputs = net(images)</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="comment"># print('*', outputs)</span></span><br><span class="line">            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs, <span class="number">1</span>)</span><br><span class="line">            c = (predicted == labels).squeeze()</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">for</span> i <span class="keyword">in</span> range(BATCH_SIZE):</span><br><span class="line">                label = labels[i]</span><br><span class="line">                class_correct[label] += c[i].item()</span><br><span class="line">                class_total[label] += <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">for</span> i <span class="keyword">in</span> range(<span class="number">10</span>):</span><br><span class="line">        print(<span class="string">'Accuracy of %5s : %2d %%'</span> % (</span><br><span class="line">            classes[i], <span class="number">100</span> * class_correct[i] / class_total[i]))</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
]]></content>
